    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "Find the spec for a module, optionally relative to the specified package name. If the module is in sys.modules, then sys.modules[name].__spec__ is returned (unless the spec would be None or is not set, in which case ValueError is raised). Otherwise a search using sys.meta_path is done. None is returned if no spec is found. If name is for a submodule (contains a dot), the parent module is automatically imported. name and package work the same as for import_module(). Added in version 3.4. Chang..."
